dismissalText.commentary: Virender Sehwag lbw b Kulasekara 12 (12b 2x4 0x6) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: big shout for lbw and given by Kumar Dharmasena! It's a huge inswinger from outside off, and although it has caught Sehwag on the back foot, it seems to be sliding down the leg side. Dharmasena takes his time and raises the finger. Sehwag is not happy, but the tracker serive shows the ball would have kissed the outside of the leg stump

and Raina is gone! Pretty similar to the one where he was not given! Perera strikes second ball. Seems like Dharmasena has made up for Rauf's mistake. Back of a length, outside off, stays low, beats Raina, snicko shows nothing, Raina is not convinced. Sri Lanka will take it - they had him in the last over

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: no need for an umpire here! not the smartest shot Dhoni has played either. Sanga goes back to standing back, and immediately Dhoni goes for a walk down the pitch, and looks to turn this to leg from way outside off. the ball holds its line enough to get the edge, and Sanga holds it safely. Dhoni walks
nine-ball duck for Jadeja! Squared up as he looks to turn this to leg from around off, and the leading edge settles safely with gully

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Karthik c Sangakkara b Kulasekara 9 (25b 0x4 0x6) SR: 36

dismissalComment.html: Kula strikes again. Good planning, good catch, or is it a catch? Sanga has been standing up to stop Karthik from walking down and negating the swing. And after pinning him in the crease, Kula has been slipping in the straighter ones to beat him outside off. This time it is very close to off, and Sanga and Kula go for a big shout right away. There is no sound as the ball passes the bat, though. Nothing on the snicko either

headshotImage.caption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023
headshotImage.longCaption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma lbw b Mathews 11 (21b 2x4 0x6) SR: 52.38

dismissalComment.html: this is so plumb Mathews doesn't even appeal! Outswinger followed by inswinger, and gone! Simple as that. This time he plays around it without any feet movement, and it hits him in front of middle. Mathews knows he is gone and turns around to appeal only after he has crossed the batsman. Don't see anything wrong with it - it was so straight. Sharma again doesn't look happy and slowly trudges off, that's becoming a bit of a habit for him. Needs to watch it - last time he got away perhaps because Randiv's act hogged the headlines. Sharma's reaction then was clear dissent, and not the first instance in his career either

batsmen.shot: off side drive on front foot

commentTextItems.html: and it's all over, Sangakkara finishes it with a lovely punch through the covers, and SL charge into the finals with a thumping win

commentPostTextItems.html: That's all we have to offer tonight. Do join us for the next game on Wednesday. Cheers
Perera is the Man of the Match He says: "I really enjoyed this match, these are my best figures. Hopefully I can carry on from this performance. I work hard on batting na dhard hitting too."

Kumar Sangakkara: "We would have batted first had we won the toss. But our bowlers, from the first ball on, bowled great lines and great lengths. We have got a varied attack. We opened with Mahela because sometimes he is wasted in the middle order. If he bats that well, we can let him bat freely at the top. This might be something we might see more often. With that amount of swing and seam, batsmen try to walk down the wicket, so I came up to deny them that feet movement. But more than that the bowlers bowled really well."

MS Dhoni to speak first of all: "We didn't get the kind of start we needed. Their bowlers bowled in the right channels, and pushed us into making the mistakes. Next game is like a semi-final now. Yuvraj batted really well. Of course he didn't get support from the other side, but good to see him in form. The only good sign in the game."

So this is Sri Lanka's seventh-best win in terms of number of balls to spare, and India's worst defeat by the same criterion. They have out-bowled, out-batted, out-fielded, out-thought, out-every-thinged India. Umpiring decisions too went their way, but that is a part of the game, and the opposition needs to take them in its stride. What a day for Perera, he used the slightly two-paced pitch superbly to complete a maiden five-for. Wait for the presentation, surely Perera will be the Man of the Match

commentTextItems.html: guides this between backward point and cover-point for two runs

headshotImage.caption: Dinesh Karthik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Karthik player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Dinesh Karthik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Karthik player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Karthik c Sangakkara b Kulasekara 9 (25b 0x4 0x6) SR: 36

dismissalComment.html: Kula strikes again. Good planning, good catch, or is it a catch? Sanga has been standing up to stop Karthik from walking down and negating the swing. And after pinning him in the crease, Kula has been slipping in the straighter ones to beat him outside off. This time it is very close to off, and Sanga and Kula go for a big shout right away. There is no sound as the ball passes the bat, though. Nothing on the snicko either

headshotImage.caption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023
headshotImage.longCaption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma lbw b Mathews 11 (21b 2x4 0x6) SR: 52.38

dismissalComment.html: this is so plumb Mathews doesn't even appeal! Outswinger followed by inswinger, and gone! Simple as that. This time he plays around it without any feet movement, and it hits him in front of middle. Mathews knows he is gone and turns around to appeal only after he has crossed the batsman. Don't see anything wrong with it - it was so straight. Sharma again doesn't look happy and slowly trudges off, that's becoming a bit of a habit for him. Needs to watch it - last time he got away perhaps because Randiv's act hogged the headlines. Sharma's reaction then was clear dissent, and not the first instance in his career either

dismissalText.commentary: Suresh Raina c Sangakkara b Perera 8 (16b 1x4 0x6) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: and Raina is gone! Pretty similar to the one where he was not given! Perera strikes second ball. Seems like Dharmasena has made up for Rauf's mistake. Back of a length, outside off, stays low, beats Raina, snicko shows nothing, Raina is not convinced. Sri Lanka will take it - they had him in the last over

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: MS Dhoni c Sangakkara b Perera 10 (16b 2x4 0x6) SR: 62.5

dismissalComment.html: no need for an umpire here! not the smartest shot Dhoni has played either. Sanga goes back to standing back, and immediately Dhoni goes for a walk down the pitch, and looks to turn this to leg from way outside off. the ball holds its line enough to get the edge, and Sanga holds it safely. Dhoni walks

headshotImage.caption: Chamara Silva player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Chamara Silva player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ravindra Jadeja c Silva b Perera 0 (9b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: nine-ball duck for Jadeja! Squared up as he looks to turn this to leg from around off, and the leading edge settles safely with gully

headshotImage.caption: Praveen Kumar, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Praveen Kumar, player page headshot cutout 2022

headshotImage.caption: Praveen Kumar, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Praveen Kumar, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalText.commentary: Praveen Kumar c Tharanga b Perera 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: and PK is gone first ball! Caught at mid-off! Perera on a hat-trick. PK looks at the pitch, then the bat. It was an extravagant drive on a back-of-a-length ball outside off. Nowhere near it. Ordinary shot, good, old tailender shot

headshotImage.caption: Ashish Nehra player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ashish Nehra player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Ashish Nehra player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ashish Nehra player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ashish Nehra c Sangakkara b Malinga 2 (4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: and he is gone! good bouncer, and he gloves it through to Sanga. SL on fire here. too good for the tailender, Nehra fends at it, and it goes off the left glove. And needless to say, Sanga is standing back for Malinga

dismissalText.commentary: Yuvraj Singh lbw b Malinga 38 (64b 5x4 1x6) SR: 59.37

dismissalComment.html: Premeditated shot. Camps on the back foot, looking to hit this - a full ball - over square-leg-midwicket region, and is hit on the back leg. Given out, but missing off clearly. It is umpire Rauf this time

dismissalText.commentary: Ishant Sharma b Perera 3 (24b 0x4 0x6) SR: 12.5

dismissalComment.html: what a beaut to finish the five-for! slightly back of a length, around off, Ishant plays for the angle, the ball holds its line to take the off stump. Perera is pleased as punch, and why shouldn't he be?

dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Jayawardene c Jadeja b I Sharma 33 (35b 6x4 0x6) SR: 94.28

dismissalComment.html: Sharma on a hat-trick! Short ball, and pulled straight to midwicket. Sri Lankans want an early finish, but these wickets are delaying proceedings

headshotImage.caption: Ashish Nehra player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ashish Nehra player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan c Nehra b I Sharma 35 (23b 8x4 0x6) SR: 152.17

dismissalComment.html: Dilshan goes! He was in too much of a hurry to finish this asap. Looks to loft it straight down the ground, but it is not full enough and he ends up skying it to mid-off

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga not out 12 (19b 2x4 0x6) SR: 63.15
Kumar Sangakkara not out 13 (15b 2x4 0x6) SR: 86.66
